Description: Shoulder and body sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery closed vessel, amphora or oinochoe; interior reserved; exterior, white slip: painted decoration consisting of part of tongue above pair of dilute bands; below, volute with multi-petalled palmette with reserved heart divided into three parts, a dot in each.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.094)
